When global supply chains are opaque, consumers lack meaningful information about where their products were made and under what conditions. Do they enable socially or environmentally irresponsible practices? Without supply chain transparency, there is just no way of knowing.

\r\n

The first step in making supply chains more transparent is mapping the supplier relationships between companies. 

" }, "methodology": { "id": 7886351, "name": "Commons+Supplier of+methodology", "type": "RichText", "url": "https://staging.wikirate.org/Commons+Supplier_of+methodology.json", "content": "

This data has been collected through semi-automated techniques. Where possible it has been scraped from supplier lists that were published by the companies.
